[{"question":"And how significant is it on a wider level that we\u0027ve now seen three of these in the last few days?","answer":"Well, Piers, it\u0027s a little difficult to tell.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":74,"aSentId":75},{"question":"From what you are assessing with your more expert eye, how worried should we be here?","answer":"Well, it\u0027s a good question.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":85,"aSentId":86},{"question":"But in terms of this latest explosion, the nuclear explosion, how worried are people where you are about the possible radiation fallout here?","answer":"I\u0027ll tell you, first of all, Piers, as happening sometimes in disaster situations, we\u0027re having a hard time actually hearing you.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":130,"aSentId":131},{"question":"But how arbitrary is that?","answer":"It seems very arbitrary.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":157,"aSentId":158},{"question":"How long is it going to be before other supplies get in here?","answer":"A very fluid situation obviously changing really by the hour, Piers.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":182,"aSentId":183},{"question":"Is this commuting down to the people on the streets?","answer":"I think it depends who you talk to and where you are.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":213,"aSentId":214},{"question":"Is it still impossible to put any real gauge on it?","answer":"It\u0027s really impossible.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":230,"aSentId":231},{"question":"Gail, where do you possibly start with a disaster on the scale of the one that we are seeing in Japan?","answer":"Well, first of all, Piers, thank you for having me on.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":256,"aSentId":257},{"question":"I mean in terms of sheer volume of natural disasters we\u0027ve seen in the last decade, how bad is this one from your perspective in terms of the work the Red Cross is needing to do to get to people there?","answer":"CGOVERN: Well, it\u0027s an absolutely amazing the extent of damage and the visuals that we see on our screen for the last 72 hours.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":266,"aSentId":267},{"question":"How much of the money that goes to the Red Cross can be guaranteed to go straight to Japan and help there?","answer":"Well, we are very proud of the fact that 91 cents of every dollar that is donated to us goes to the relief efforts in the country that we\u0027re targeting.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":277,"aSentId":278},{"question":"What is the priority for the Red Cross right now?","answer":"Well, right now food, shelter, medical supplies.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":285,"aSentId":286},{"question":"Where were you?","answer":"Well, I was in New York, of course.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":318,"aSentId":319},{"question":"And how did you hear the news?","answer":"Well, like you heard it, too, I suppose, through the -- through the TV news.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":320,"aSentId":321},{"question":"Can you believe what you\u0027re seeing?","answer":"I just can\u0027t believe it.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":322,"aSentId":323},{"question":"What did it feel like?","answer":"NO: Well, I was so scared.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":331,"aSentId":332},{"question":"What was it look for you?","answer":"That one was very -- pretty bad.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":346,"aSentId":347},{"question":"Are they all OK?","answer":"Because most of them are in Tokyo, and Tokyo was all right in a way.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":355,"aSentId":356},{"question":"Is that very much the Japanese culture to react that way?","answer":"Well, they\u0027re not violent people.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":370,"aSentId":371},{"question":"What would you say to them?","answer":"We\u0027re all together in spirit.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":384,"aSentId":385},{"question":"What is the best way for Americans in particular to help here?","answer":"Well, as of now, I found that there\u0027s no definite funds -- foundation in Japan that we can send money to.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":392,"aSentId":393},{"question":"People are going to struggle to keep positive and helpful there, aren\u0027t they?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":400,"aSentId":401},{"question":"Can any country be ready for an attack of a natural disaster like this?","answer":"I think it\u0027s too far.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":427,"aSentId":428},{"question":"How vulnerable are they to a similar perfect storm of earthquake and tsunami causing the kind of partial meltdowns that we\u0027re seeing?","answer":"Well, the one thing that we do -- and this was after the Three Mile Island incident -- is the Nuclear Regulatory Commission and the Federal Emergency Management Agency required that each licensed operator conduct annual exercises, as well as drills.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":440,"aSentId":441},{"question":"What are the key lessons that you are learning watching what is happening in Japan, for a similar situation potentially one day happening in America?","answer":"Probably the one thing that you have heard time and time again from your guests is how resilient the Japanese population is.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":445,"aSentId":446},{"question":"Do you agree with him, that we are in a relatively strong position in America?","answer":"Well, I agree with him that things have been improved since 9/11 and certainly since Katrina.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":453,"aSentId":454},{"question":"Do you have any way of predicting where the most likely places are that may suffer this thing?","answer":"Sure.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":465,"aSentId":466},{"question":"Where are we talking about?","answer":"Well, places like the central U.S. and places you may not think about, such as fault lines that occur in other parts of the country that don\u0027t have a lot of activity, but have had significant historical events, such as down in Charleston, South Carolina and other places.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":471,"aSentId":472},{"question":"What does this mean for the American nuclear energy project?","answer":"Well, it\u0027s going to be tough days ahead for the nuclear power industry.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":512,"aSentId":513},{"question":"Or would you be suspicious the situation may be worse than we\u0027re told?","answer":"You never believe everything you\u0027re hearing, but we don\u0027t spy on the Japanese.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":527,"aSentId":528},{"question":"One of the issues here is that there will be terrorist organizations around the world looking at the vulnerability of these nuclear plants and looking at them as potential ultimate dirty bombs, won\u0027t they?","answer":"Well, if they can get hold of some of the material for dirty bombs, yes.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":544,"aSentId":545},{"question":"Governor Richardson, very quickly here, what would you say are the key lessons that America needs to learn in terms of its energy program from what we\u0027ve seen in Japan in the last few days?","answer":"Number one, we have to recognize that we need to move toward more diverse sources of energy.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":555,"aSentId":556},{"question":"How worried are people on the ground there?","answer":"Piers, I\u0027ve got to say that people are starting to get worried.","docId":"110314pmt","qSentId":569,"aSentId":570}]